OL,3,GWales
OL,4,
OL,5,CToday:FSome low cloud first thing,
OL,6,Fwith perhaps an isolated light shower
OL,7,Fin the south. Skies brightening by
OL,8,Flunchtime, with plenty of sunshine
OL,9,Fdeveloping. Generally feeling fresher
OL,10,Fthan of late though temperatures
OL,11,Fstaying above the May average.
OL,12,
OL,13,CTonight:FClearer skies for many
OL,14,Fovernight which will allow
OL,15,Ftemperatures to fall, giving a much
OL,16,Fmore comfortable night for many.
OL,17,FStaying dry with mist and fog in
OL,18,Fplaces.
OL,23,QppppppppppppppppppppGSource: Met Office
OL,24,ANext Page  BWeather  CReg News  FReg TV
